    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1877-10-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1877-10-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="168" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d168">
                <head>No. 163.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Pierrepont</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1877-10-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 25, 1877</date>.
                            (Received November 7.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 238.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have finally concluded a trade-mark
                        convention with the Earl of Derby, excluding all the objectionable words
                        about which I wrote in my dispatch No. 191. The convention was signed in
                        duplicate yesterday at half past three o’clock at the foreign office, and I
                        forward the same herewith to-day.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>EDWARDS PIERREPONT.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
